------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Install System Dependencies
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install libcgal-dev libgeos-dev pr-openrave
sudo pip install colorlog descartes progressbar matplotlib numpy scipy shapely

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Install Boost.Numpy
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

cd /tmp
git clone https://github.com/personalrobotics/Boost.NumPy.git
cd Boost.NumPy
cmake -DCPACK_GENERATOR=DEB .
make && make package
sudo dpkg -i boost-numpy-*.deb

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Install Boost.Numpy_Eigen
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

cd /tmp
git clone https://github.com/personalrobotics/Boost.NumPy_Eigen.git
cd Boost.NumPy_Eigen
cmake -DCPACK_GENERATOR=DEB .
make && make package
sudo dpkg -i boost-numpy-eigen-*.deb

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Install Gazebo
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

sudo sh -c 'echo "deb http://packages.osrfoundation.org/gazebo/ubuntu precise main" > /etc/apt/sources.list.d/gazebo-latest.list'
wget http://packages.osrfoundation.org/gazebo.key -O - | sudo apt-key add -
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install gazebo-current

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Install ROS Packages
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

git clone into a catkin workspace using:
   git@github.com:personalrobotics/kenv.git
   or
   https://github.com/personalrobotics/kenv.git

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Export Plugin Location
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

export GAZEBO_PLUGIN_PATH=${GAZEBO_PLUGIN_PATH}: (workspace directory)/devel/lib/	

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Adding Quasistatic Physics to a World
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

To set objects usign quasistatic physics

Using SDF:

Plugin Tag for gazebo_quasistatic_plugin must have 2 types of elements. 1 of tag type <pusher> and 1 or more of tag type <pushee>. 

Using Transport Layer:

library is called libquasistatic_msgs.so and is apart of the gazebo_quasistatic_plugin package

proto_msg/set_pusher_request.proto
proto_msg/add_pushee_request.proto

The topic names respectively are
quasistatic_set_pusher
quasistatic_add_pushee

=== Model Plugin ===
The pusher will not move on its own so a model plugin is needed to command its motion.  Quasistatic physics only is concerned with the motion of pushees

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Example World
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

kenv/gazebo_quasistatic_plugin/models/blank_world.world

